In a message dated 3/30/03 11:37:03 PM Central Standard Time, 
roborick007@... writes:


> : : Rodimus Prime : : Rodimus took notice of Maxima comeing at him. He 
> recognized the voice from the past. Rodimus Prime: Can't say I'm happy to 
> see you functioning. Now out of my way you Decepticon b*tch! Maxima's 
> attack had a very big flaw. Although she managed to slice a bit of Rodimus' 
> hood, she failed to realize what a sports care going at speeds over 200mph 
> would do. He simply plowed into her without careing in the least for the 
> Decepticon femme. This would surely cause some heavy damage to Maxima. 
> 
> 

Knocked away from Windlord, as the hulking form of Rodimus throw her back 
quite a ways. Letting out a feline yelp/growl as her form slid & rolled away 
from the collision she sustained from Rodimus. 

Wincing, she growled. Yeah... it did cause damage ... that & it was quite 
painful. Struggling to get up, she collapsed. Then attempted to get up 
again... her clear blue optics glared at Rodimus, through her teeth, she bit 
out, "I'm not that easy to put down... Auto-FOOL!" 

Despite something that Hydras told her some time ago, she dismissed it 
quickly. She was a Decepticon. She had continued to function this long... 
there was NO way that this Autobot will take her down now. 

She stood partly up, & pulled out her tail, as it seperated into 2 components 
- 2  energy swords. She threw them both at Rodimus. "Ashes to ashes.. 
Rodimus! Just like PRIME!" One destroyed Leader for vengence for another. It 
was still a very sour & sore spot to her... Megatron's demise.... becoming 
Galvatron... the isolation... the torture... nothingness.... Yes, Rodimus was 
a part of it, & she would make sure he would pay for it all. 

--part1_15f.1e30c06c.2bb93186_boundary
